| Notes                   = * This is the first film in the ''Deadpool'' franchise to take place in the [[Earth-199999|Marvel Cinematic Universe]], and it is also the first film in the MCU to be rated-R.
* Originally slated to be released on September 6, 2024, the film was rescheduled to be released on November 8{{cite|ref=true|url= https://deadline.com/2022/10/blade-fantastic-four-avengers-secret-wars-release-dates-shift-1235141388/|title= Marvel Shifts Release Dates For ‚ÄòBlade‚Äô, ‚ÄòFantastic Four‚Äô, ‚ÄòAvengers: Secret Wars‚Äô, Next ‚ÄòDeadpool‚Äô Among Disney Moves|work= Deadline|last= Grobar|first= Matt|date= October 11, 2022|accessdate= October 12, 2022}} and later May 3 of that same year,{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/disney-moves-avatar-star-wars-avengers-1235514145/|title=‚ÄòAvatar 3‚Äô Pushed a Year to 2025, Two ‚ÄòStar Wars‚Äô Movies Head for 2026 and ‚ÄòAvengers‚Äô Films Delayed|work=The Hollywood Reporter|last=Couch|first=Aaron|date=June 13, 2023|accessdate=June 13, 2023}} before finally landing its July 26, 2024 release date.{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/movies/movie-news/deadpool-3-release-dates-captain-america-1235643159/|title=‚ÄòDeadpool 3‚Äô, ‚ÄòCaptain America 4‚Äô Among Marvel Release Date Changes as Strike Ends|work=The Hollywood Reporter|last=Couch|first=Aaron|date=November 9, 2023|accessdate=November 10, 2023}}
* While the film identified [[Earth-10005 Revised|Deadpool's home reality]] as "[[Earth-10005]]," presumably based on the designation which was assigned to the original {{ml|X-Men (film)}} in the {{cl|Official Handbook of the Marvel Universe A to Z Vol 1 4}}, it was established in [[X-Men: Days of Future Past (film)|X-Men: Days of Future Past]] as a revised timeline diverging from [[Earth-10005|original timeline's history]] in 1973.
* The film also identifies the events of the film ''[[Logan (film)|Logan]]'' as taking place within "[[Earth-10005 Revised|Earth-10005]]" though it had previously been identified as taking place in the [[Earth-17315|future]]. This can be explained as Earth-17315 only being a possible future{{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.digitalspy.com/movies/a819480/hugh-jackman-says-logan-different-universe-x-men-films/|title=Logan is not set in the same universe as the X-Men movies, says Hugh Jackman|work=Digital Spy|first=Rosie|last=Fletcher|date=January 21, 2017|accessdate=October 12, 2024|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/nXnFQ|archivedate=October 12, 2024}}{{cite|ref=true|url=https://comicbook.com/marvel/news/logan-director-james-mangold-x-men-sequels-franchise-future/|title=Logan Director On The X-Men Franchise‚Äôs Open Future ][‚ÄúI gave them many escape valves. We take place in 2029, and X-Men [Days of Future Past] ends in 2024,‚Äù Mangold said. ‚ÄúThere‚Äôs five blank years there that are wide open to seeing how things got from here to there. Or else you could do what I would advocate, which is imagine a different world and create a new movie, and you don‚Äôt need the permission of the other movies.|work=ComicBook.com|first=Joseph|last=Schmidt|date=September 5, 2017|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/9xgie|archivedate=November 17, 2024}}{{cite|ref=true|url=http://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/logan-11-revelations-director-james-mangold/|title=Logan: 11 Revelations From Director James Mangold|work=Empire|first=John|last=Nugent|date=March 7, 2017|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170909065225/http://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/logan-11-revelations-director-james-mangold/|archivedate=September 8, 2017}}{{cite|ref=true|url=https://twitter.com/mang0ld/status/871482277045207040|title=James Mangold on Twitter: "Not a dystopian possibility. Simply a possibility."|work=twitter|first=James|last=Mangold|date=January 21, 2017|archiveurl=https://vignette.wikia.nocookie.net/marveldatabase/images/5/5e/20240819%EF%BC%BF171728.png/revision/latest?cb=20240825140314&format=original|archivedate=August 25, 2024}}{{cite|ref=true|url=https://twitter.com/mang0ld/status/823196909707751425|title=James Mangold on Twitter: "Because we take place after all the other movies, we have freedom. That's all he meant. Breathe,"|work=twitter|first=James|last=Mangold|date=January 23, 2017|accessdate=October 21, 2024|archiveurl=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/ttoXf|archivedate=October 21, 2024}} and from the TVA's perspective, given they exist outside conventional time, the main events there already happened.

| Trivia                  = * The movie's ending was tweaked during reshoots at the urging of [[Ryan Reynolds]]' wife {{WP|Blake Lively}}. Originally, [[Wade Wilson (Earth-10005 Revised)|Deadpool]] and [[James Howlett (Earth-TRN1400)|Wolverine]]'s survival after destroying the [[Time Ripper]] was never in question, as they are immediately shown to have survived the film's climax. According to director {{WP|Shawn Levy}}, Lively urged for the movie to linger on revealing the titular character's survival, expressing, "You know, I've been with you this whole movie. I want to sit in the fear that they're lost. Let me be in that place of suspense so the triumph of their survival is more emotional and visceral." The reshot content included [[Paradox (Null-Time Zone)|Mr. Paradox]]'s impassioned speech before he is disrupted by the heroes' return to the {{WP|Goo Goo Dolls}}' {{WP|Iris (song)|"Iris."}}{{cite|ref=true|url=https://variety.com/2024/film/news/deadpool-and-wolverine-ending-changed-blake-lively-note-reshoots-1236214224/|title=‚ÄòDeadpool & Wolverine‚Äô Tweaked Its Ending During 36 Hours of Reshoots and After a Note From Blake Lively: ‚ÄòLet Me Be in That Place of Suspense‚Äô More|work=Variety|first=Zack|last=Sharf|date=November 19, 2024|accessdate=November 22, 2024|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20241121082249/https://variety.com/2024/film/news/deadpool-and-wolverine-ending-changed-blake-lively-note-reshoots-1236214224/|archivedate=November 21, 2024}}
*Stunt performer David McDonald was cast and filmed as a variant of [[Nicholas Fury (Earth-5724)|David Hasselhoff's Nick Fury]], but his scenes were cut from the final film. Fury's appearance during the battle with Cassandra Nova's Henchmen is still present in the script. {{cite|ref=true|url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/movies/news/deadpool-wolverine-set-photo-reveals-white-nick-fury-variants-deleted-cameo/ar-AA1rfyfi?apiversion=v2&noservercache=1&domshim=1&renderwebcomponents=1&wcseo=1&batchservertelemetry=1&noservertelemetry=1|title=Deadpool & Wolverine Set Photo Reveals White Nick Fury Variant's Deleted Cameo|Work=MSN|first=Anubhav|last=Chaudhry|date=September 26, 2024|access date=April 1, 2025}}

